<entry id="abu" guid="b1181446-8863-58e1-88ca-b5107727561e"><lexical-unit><form lang="id"><text>abu</text></form></lexical-unit><trait name="morph-type" value="stem"/><sense id="abu_0" guid="e55ad985-af43-5808-9f25-3fa6dd595e9a"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>ash (solid remains of a fire)</text></gloss></sense><sense id="abu_1" guid="bfa7a4e5-53f0-57f4-9c2e-44de0f5fcce0"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>synonym of debu (“dust”)</text></gloss></sense><sense id="abu_2" guid="08555959-47d0-597f-9e2b-ebcc875d063d"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>to have defeat</text></gloss></sense><sense id="abu_3" guid="f5ffad46-f5c8-5c8b-97c0-2404aa621390"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>synonym of ayah (“father”)</text></gloss></sense><sense id="abu_4" guid="4259f790-40c1-547a-9da3-4fb8123362eb"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>to lose (in the game of congklak, spinning top)</text></gloss></sense><sense id="abu_5" guid="cbd3f17e-4682-5939-86d1-a8f059c7e823"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>the way to store a baby's placenta by placing it in a sago palm leaf and tucking it between tree branches so that it is not eaten by ground animals.</text></gloss></sense><sense id="abu_6" guid="f551c1ac-8511-5601-a1ea-a01ca7db2f60"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>alternative form of abuan</text></gloss></sense></entry>
