Apa dia ngerti?
Does he understand?</text></gloss></sense><sense id="apa_4" guid="f627d2bd-9f2b-561b-83f5-5e66380f86e3"><grammatical-info value="Pronoun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>Apa dia ngerti?</text></gloss></sense><sense id="apa_5" guid="7f8456e3-cdb4-590f-8da7-f0fcc7da3aa3"><grammatical-info value="Pronoun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>Does he understand?</text></gloss></sense><sense id="apa_6" guid="d40af1ab-4ac9-52ba-b53b-82fcd9625c55"><grammatical-info value="Pronoun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>what (fused relative)</text></gloss></sense><sense id="apa_7" guid="7ae0766b-1ae3-53b6-9f58-83be6530c014"><grammatical-info value="Pronoun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>what?</text></gloss></sense></entry>
<entry id="apabila" guid="33c0e1fb-3459-556c-89fd-81bd679fe790"><lexical-unit><form lang="id"><text>apabila</text></form></lexical-unit><trait name="morph-type" value="stem"/><sense id="apabila_0" guid="cff2a4a0-4c9c-51a4-b8be-95a8ce43c113"><grammatical-info value="Subordinating connective"/><gloss lang="en"><text>if</text></gloss></sense><sense id="apabila_1" guid="fca59b53-247f-5df1-8ae4-5240a4075e0a"><grammatical-info value="Subordinating connective"/><gloss lang="en"><text>when</text></gloss></sense></entry>
<entry id="apalagi" guid="bad926a1-24d9-556b-980b-ccd0539d0e58"><lexical-unit><form lang="id"><text>apalagi</text></form></lexical-unit><trait name="morph-type" value="stem"/><sense id="apalagi_0" guid="f142b7a4-baa3-5db5-8e68-ad7b480f6a7f"><grammatical-info value="Adverb"/><gloss lang="en"><text>especially</text></gloss></sense><sense id="apalagi_1" guid="94708839-4e75-51ed-bcce-65ff1abab736"><grammatical-info value="Adverb"/><gloss lang="en"><text>let alone</text></gloss></sense></entry>
<entry id="apel" guid="e1860a0a-3a9e-5cb6-8c86-798c883a8657"><lexical-unit><form lang="id"><text>apel</text></form></lexical-unit><trait name="morph-type" value="stem"/><sense id="apel_0" guid="c32817e3-244d-5995-b1ba-dcf5fd87b691"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>apple, Malus domestica</text></gloss></sense><sense id="apel_1" guid="3f509fd9-88bb-5fd0-bff5-d55dd4946042"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>roll call</text></gloss></sense><sense id="apel_2" guid="23133181-7189-57a6-86db-043ddafbbcda"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>a ceremony formation (for roll call).</text></gloss></sense><sense id="apel_3" guid="2fa67a95-797e-507d-9065-ac12a59d216d"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>sub-village chief</text></gloss></sense><sense id="apel_4" guid="78bac039-9e68-5b6e-88fb-2c30684daf43"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>appeal: an application for the removal of a cause or suit from an inferior to a superior judge or court for re-examination or review</text></gloss></sense><sense id="apel_5" guid="816bb5a5-427f-5d31-a91a-e18d98ca21f9"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>to do a roll call in a ceremony formation</text></gloss></sense><sense id="apel_6" guid="e05931f0-323a-5f78-8162-851c60cfca3a"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>to visit girlfriend (usually in girlfriend house) for a date</text></gloss></sense><sense id="apel_7" guid="552f9ae6-3ebd-52a7-a194-6c86650c9fea"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>to appeal: to apply to a superior court or judge for a decision or order by an inferior court or judge to be reviewed and overturned.</text></gloss></sense></entry>
<entry id="api" guid="38c34e16-9b3c-50f6-81c5-c9c983da22da"><lexical-unit><form lang="id"><text>api</text></form></lexical-unit><trait name="morph-type" value="stem"/><sense id="api_0" guid="044e46f2-725f-5f57-acbf-e31e82736f2b"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>fire</text></gloss></sense><sense id="api_1" guid="4b39b8a5-21c9-52e2-8b37-d2884fe1fdca"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>fire (the occurrence, often accidental, of fire in a certain place, causing damage and danger)</text></gloss></sense><sense id="api_2" guid="a48f3ea8-f348-5e56-a4db-28e34f58cdcf"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>fire (strength of passion, whether love or hate)</text></gloss></sense><sense id="api_3" guid="caf6fa83-ae66-5690-a386-b219da84ec55"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>initialism of Akademi Penerbang Indonesia</text></gloss></sense><sense id="api_4" guid="fedcf515-d4f9-516d-882c-66ddeaf4147f"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>initialism of alat penangkapan ikan</text></gloss></sense><sense id="api_5" guid="ad0e0a90-f94b-567b-8a7d-30340b9a0d07"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>Initialism of application programming interface.</text></gloss></sense><sense id="api_6" guid="19ddcc63-dbfd-5a37-a65a-86eb6bd48f01"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>initialism of Anugerah Pesona Indonesia</text></gloss></sense><sense id="api_7" guid="7daa4ec7-d194-5364-a3c6-d403c8311f4f"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>initialism of angka pengenal importir</text></gloss></sense></entry>
<entry id="ara" guid="ce2f09e5-abdf-53a0-ba0e-9977c6f46ae0"><lexical-unit><form lang="id"><text>ara</text></form></lexical-unit><trait name="morph-type" value="stem"/><sense id="ara_0" guid="27f6c688-e47b-54ae-90b7-1db49ca92b04"><grammatical-info value="Proper noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>fig (tree or shrub)</text></gloss></sense><sense id="ara_1" guid="4c6757c9-d3b2-5690-a1f1-b0a10d98f9b5"><grammatical-info value="Proper noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>green figbird, Timor figbird (Sphecotheres viridis)</text></gloss></sense></entry>
<entry id="arab" guid="e7417a8b-c584-5baa-a2e3-e011631c0675"><lexical-unit><form lang="id"><text>arab</text></form></lexical-unit><trait name="morph-type" value="stem"/><sense id="arab_0" guid="4a2ed176-cf20-548b-92ba-623be415e175"><grammatical-info value="Proper noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>Arabic</text></gloss></sense><sense id="arab_1" guid="3cd5ac70-92ea-55a8-88b8-3253afc6f009"><grammatical-info value="Proper noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>Arabian, Arab</text></gloss></sense><sense id="arab_2" guid="3ba53197-3c0d-5665-be42-74b99df49f07"><grammatical-info value="Proper noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>Arabic, a major Semitic language originating from the Arabian peninsula</text></gloss></sense><sense id="arab_3" guid="66e716ae-f61b-5b84-ba71-6765976b723a"><grammatical-info value="Proper noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>Arabia</text></gloss></sense><sense id="arab_4" guid="fb8d9332-54e8-5107-bbf8-4c497aee205a"><grammatical-info value="Proper noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>ellipsis of Arab Saudi</text></gloss></sense></entry>
<entry id="arah" guid="6270ab17-0250-5a2c-830e-e2c2b6c87247"><lexical-unit><form lang="id"><text>arah</text></form></lexical-unit><trait name="morph-type" value="stem"/><sense id="arah_0" guid="6a3a99e3-0cef-5150-a50d-5b0c72ddab80"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>direction</text></gloss></sense><sense id="arah_1" guid="57e0b132-bfe2-55ff-8f20-a404d9339c42"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>purpose</text></gloss></sense></entry>
<entry id="aram" guid="cf910c81-53a8-5ac9-935f-eee15d935dc8"><lexical-unit><form lang="id"><text>aram</text></form></lexical-unit><trait name="morph-type" value="stem"/><sense id="aram_0" guid="0b057866-5293-5791-b479-ad5a3bb33fde"><grammatical-info value="Proper noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>Aram (a historical region mentioned in early cuneiforms and in the Bible, located in modern Syria as well as parts of Iraq, Lebanon and southeastern Turkey; inhabited by Arameans)</text></gloss></sense></entry>
<entry id="are" guid="97d2c104-2f51-5001-b610-dc2971bd51e4"><lexical-unit><form lang="id"><text>are</text></form></lexical-unit><trait name="morph-type" value="stem"/><sense id="are_0" guid="c0872461-6a66-5f07-93c2-e3b04ee9396e"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>are; an SI unit of area equal to 100 square metres, or a former unit of approximately the same extent</text></gloss></sense></entry>
<entry id="aretas" guid="c07e24c5-3141-5c6f-b530-d2786f35130e"><lexical-unit><form lang="id"><text>aretas</text></form></lexical-unit><trait name="morph-type" value="stem"/><sense id="aretas_0" guid="0712ce37-8e1f-5771-8ffe-9addd6f631b5"><grammatical-info value="Proper noun"/></sense></entry>
<entry id="argumen" guid="82d6a123-649a-5c8c-a4fa-f290bf74290f"><lexical-unit><form lang="id"><text>argumen</text></form></lexical-unit><trait name="morph-type" value="stem"/><sense id="argumen_0" guid="d3e83873-56e0-5b76-ab1f-5dde4e9c7219"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>argument:</text></gloss></sense><sense id="argumen_1" guid="42306f31-1bae-53b3-9ee3-566041cd8376"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>reason: a fact or statement used to support a proposition</text></gloss></sense><sense id="argumen_2" guid="b9a27603-9b63-5928-bb17-8c1e8aea1799"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>any of the phrases that bears a syntactic connection to the verb of a clause</text></gloss></sense></entry>
<entry id="ari" guid="05ea3de0-d547-5f59-ae08-153c1e82529f"><lexical-unit><form lang="id"><text>ari</text></form></lexical-unit><trait name="morph-type" value="stem"/><sense id="ari_0" guid="0350acd2-33c4-540c-8f3b-fe11acae621c"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>stable (a building, wing or dependency set apart and adapted for lodging and feeding (and training) ungulates, especially horses)</text></gloss></sense><sense id="ari_1" guid="4ae07937-8fa4-5333-b24b-fc839c1fbcc8"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>to tether (to restrict with, or as if, with a tether)</text></gloss></sense><sense id="ari_2" guid="60ee8797-8bee-59cf-83b9-d4ae17194dfa"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>a thin layer; can be roughly translated as lamina</text></gloss></sense><sense id="ari_3" guid="a3b5615b-5061-5d33-8038-0ba0b729cdc8"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>ellipsis of ular ari (“a kind of snake”)</text></gloss></sense><sense id="ari_4" guid="73ac0cbc-2468-5d6a-afbd-b521ae1088f3"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>a male given name from Old Javanese</text></gloss></sense><sense id="ari_5" guid="6fe0394e-d4ec-5069-8391-105510965195"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>alternative form of hari (“day”)</text></gloss></sense></entry>
<entry id="arik" guid="f52901c1-08c1-501e-b1a7-fca38d63e887"><lexical-unit><form lang="id"><text>arik</text></form></lexical-unit><trait name="morph-type" value="stem"/><sense id="arik_0" guid="2e7a9dc2-7a24-5ad5-b756-5e9e8959d404"><grammatical-info value="Proper noun"/></sense></entry>
<entry id="aroma" guid="470145fe-7f8d-58ea-9b0a-7ac72b32d027"><lexical-unit><form lang="id"><text>aroma</text></form></lexical-unit><trait name="morph-type" value="stem"/><sense id="aroma_0" guid="6757027f-7d50-5c2d-8422-0e1a45607ad1"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>aroma: smell; especially a pleasant spicy or fragrant one</text></gloss></sense><sense id="aroma_1" guid="9963ddc5-55c0-5466-8252-b921d8f5df03"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>food flavouring</text></gloss></sense><sense id="aroma_2" guid="782d0f86-4ae3-564f-8b5e-019bbddedf82"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>nature, characteristic</text></gloss></sense></entry>
<entry id="art" guid="b9a75bf9-c665-5090-ba96-09838235cea0"><lexical-unit><form lang="id"><text>art</text></form></lexical-unit><trait name="morph-type" value="stem"/><sense id="art_0" guid="48c3969d-fb58-5d1c-9036-0066f79e869e"><grammatical-info value="Proper noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>initialism of anggaran rumah tangga</text></gloss></sense><sense id="art_1" guid="2cf22031-cd44-59cf-8c8b-070855d91732"><grammatical-info value="Proper noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>initialism of asisten rumah tangga</text></gloss></sense></entry>
<entry id="arti" guid="98fd9734-b930-5206-9026-7273b53bef65"><lexical-unit><form lang="id"><text>arti</text></form></lexical-unit><trait name="morph-type" value="stem"/><sense id="arti_0" guid="f0551c18-7e9f-5c0b-985b-f3e789a25eec"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>meaning</text></gloss></sense><sense id="arti_1" guid="17b31e68-5d46-5eeb-a2dc-560c8731483b"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>the denotation, referent, or idea connected with a word, expression, or symbol</text></gloss></sense><sense id="arti_2" guid="801ef295-9219-59e3-b368-8e4ffb23f32a"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>the connotation associated with a word, expression, or symbol</text></gloss></sense><sense id="arti_3" guid="08b56f7f-b3fa-5166-b571-5347eddb2d1d"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>the purpose, value, or significance (of something) beyond the fact of that thing's existence</text></gloss></sense><sense id="arti_4" guid="128608dd-19fd-5b17-8cda-d58b2f4e694c"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>sense (any particular meaning of a word, among its various meanings)</text></gloss></sense></entry>
<entry id="aruh" guid="7619186b-9c38-5e73-9159-fbd0bc366c50"><lexical-unit><form lang="id"><text>aruh</text></form></lexical-unit><trait name="morph-type" value="stem"/><sense id="aruh_0" guid="021aa4e4-3fcd-5a68-9f40-0bafbfeeef2e"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>greeting</text></gloss></sense></entry>
<entry id="as" guid="d9f52414-8a25-5b5b-ad83-844b9ced21eb"><lexical-unit><form lang="id"><text>as</text></form></lexical-unit><trait name="morph-type" value="stem"/><sense id="as_0" guid="29b3a69f-587f-55d4-a225-8d86849bf6f4"><grammatical-info value="Proper noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>axis</text></gloss></sense><sense id="as_1" guid="df18792f-e824-5f89-b597-cc70c597a779"><grammatical-info value="Proper noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>axle (the pin or spindle on which a wheel revolves, or which revolves with a wheel)</text></gloss></sense><sense id="as_2" guid="ab88ba84-e96b-55de-b7ba-3db13a881902"><grammatical-info value="Proper noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>axle, axletree (a transverse bar or shaft connecting the opposite wheels of a car or carriage)</text></gloss></sense><sense id="as_3" guid="b63cfa95-f05d-591e-bb00-c41bb19dd5ee"><grammatical-info value="Proper noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>propeller shaft in fishing boat</text></gloss></sense><sense id="as_4" guid="b567fa72-c52d-5a66-bdd6-ee1ebfc508f1"><grammatical-info value="Proper noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>ace</text></gloss></sense><sense id="as_5" guid="926fa168-081f-54c0-b75e-402e0c039859"><grammatical-info value="Proper noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>card with a single spot</text></gloss></sense><sense id="as_6" guid="3f0d6514-5b01-5d4e-b5fc-c5ca3d190bcf"><grammatical-info value="Proper noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>point scored without the opponent hitting the ball</text></gloss></sense><sense id="as_7" guid="d000efa1-9a46-575a-9d75-44cec64be397"><grammatical-info value="Proper noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>a hole in one</text></gloss></sense></entry>
<entry id="asa" guid="515a405c-07f6-596a-9b32-8a33048bfb6d"><lexical-unit><form lang="id"><text>asa</text></form></lexical-unit><trait name="morph-type" value="stem"/><sense id="asa_0" guid="6fc0040c-83a6-5eea-b01b-5c2b61afd85e"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>synonym of harapan (“hope”)</text></gloss></sense><sense id="asa_1" guid="3dd06a6d-a20b-58d8-ab0e-85fac9b8722f"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>synonym of sangka (“to think, guess, suspect”)</text></gloss></sense><sense id="asa_2" guid="bfec0bbd-4715-51d1-ac63-5ff8453c3590"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>synonym of sengaja (“intentionally”)</text></gloss></sense><sense id="asa_3" guid="d25ad418-d402-5ad1-acbd-3258b6ab1b9a"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>a roof seam, made of coconut leaves</text></gloss></sense></entry>
<entry id="asal" guid="d9d60b28-40dc-519f-a61d-c90afa4421f0"><lexical-unit><form lang="id"><text>asal</text></form></lexical-unit><trait name="morph-type" value="stem"/><sense id="asal_0" guid="544b3424-fef5-5bbe-ba81-8e524e21e41c"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>origin</text></gloss></sense><sense id="asal_1" guid="cce9f6f8-0f93-574d-b3bf-2624ce40d481"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>the beginning of something</text></gloss></sense><sense id="asal_2" guid="faf2de45-2f44-5371-b23c-9c42fc914472"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>the source of a river, information, goods, etc.</text></gloss></sense><sense id="asal_3" guid="3b4e96e7-8922-5b3c-8649-826a823d7b45"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>if (on the condition that)</text></gloss></sense><sense id="asal_4" guid="b3325576-45da-5ff6-9cea-40807c23e07b"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>from the beginning; from the start</text></gloss></sense><sense id="asal_5" guid="3d626b69-51ad-5bf7-b1ad-9f1b00bdf9b1"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>careless (not giving sufficient attention or thought, especially concerning the avoidance of harm or mistakes)</text></gloss></sense></entry>
<entry id="asam" guid="8249927c-309b-5d99-8a7f-aa5a8b72c490"><lexical-unit><form lang="id"><text>asam</text></form></lexical-unit><trait name="morph-type" value="stem"/><sense id="asam_0" guid="5f096fea-ea6f-5b03-a142-0f8c195d179c"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>sour, acid, acidic, tangy</text></gloss></sense><sense id="asam_1" guid="9144cab4-22f1-5413-9d95-7d32df3fa84a"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>sourfaced</text></gloss></sense><sense id="asam_2" guid="c9091694-b73f-5321-8bd2-375faaca63e1"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>acidic (of or pertaining to an acid)</text></gloss></sense><sense id="asam_3" guid="c375632e-879c-595c-a6fb-c6fce8f64cdb"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>tamarind (Tamarindus indica)</text></gloss></sense><sense id="asam_4" guid="576fc078-4fe4-52bc-8c18-00eaebb1037a"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>sour</text></gloss></sense><sense id="asam_5" guid="f95d3634-deff-58b9-8378-c4894fb3a870"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>acid</text></gloss></sense></entry>
<entry id="asap" guid="609783c9-4f73-55b7-9e9a-d9f3edc9e0ce"><lexical-unit><form lang="id"><text>asap</text></form></lexical-unit><trait name="morph-type" value="stem"/><sense id="asap_0" guid="7de181fe-e77c-5106-b750-e6cfd9122f4a"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>smoke</text></gloss></sense><sense id="asap_1" guid="4889639f-a539-572f-96cc-8030cdba1af0"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>smoked (preserved by treatment with smoke)</text></gloss></sense><sense id="asap_2" guid="4e8d39dc-e7cf-55b2-8766-0a3ba95a2da8"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>to smoke (to preserve or prepare by treating with smoke)</text></gloss></sense><sense id="asap_3" guid="f4d44693-03f7-555c-b5fe-e39da7b2b0ea"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>to smoke (to give off smoke)</text></gloss></sense><sense id="asap_4" guid="76392c2d-bdad-5260-999b-5e9fba5e4388"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>initialism of Englishas soon as possible</text></gloss></sense></entry>
<entry id="asas" guid="abcd221c-83f0-5bc0-9699-8237fe1c72f5"><lexical-unit><form lang="id"><text>asas</text></form></lexical-unit><trait name="morph-type" value="stem"/><sense id="asas_0" guid="945f7b26-d49f-515e-8386-d7eabbb2e75f"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>principle</text></gloss></sense><sense id="asas_1" guid="28577135-176a-5de3-afc3-f3b420ee954f"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>base</text></gloss></sense></entry>
<entry id="asia" guid="fe00760e-1ed1-599c-80a3-37879d384a1c"><lexical-unit><form lang="id"><text>asia</text></form></lexical-unit><trait name="morph-type" value="stem"/><sense id="asia_0" guid="eafa3511-f7de-5ab0-9dac-62e4e32a04d2"><grammatical-info value="Proper noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>Asia (the largest continent, located between Europe and the Pacific Ocean)</text></gloss></sense><sense id="asia_1" guid="a6af895d-c88e-51d5-a974-2f15ba1cdcad"><grammatical-info value="Proper noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>Asia (an ancient province of the Roman Empire in western Anatolia, existing between 133 BC (during the Roman Republic) and the 7th century AD)</text></gloss></sense></entry>
<entry id="asin" guid="4ccccb00-2be4-57cd-b682-24f885691295"><lexical-unit><form lang="id"><text>asin</text></form></lexical-unit><trait name="morph-type" value="stem"/><sense id="asin_0" guid="58b76d3c-e9c1-513e-bf23-3497ed1117b6"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>salty (tasting of salt)</text></gloss></sense></entry>
<entry id="asing" guid="06ff4b6d-2db9-5cab-8c4e-53e93efb347e"><lexical-unit><form lang="id"><text>asing</text></form></lexical-unit><trait name="morph-type" value="stem"/><sense id="asing_0" guid="7d7fb295-14ce-55a2-927d-53a172d880b9"><grammatical-info value="Adjective"/><gloss lang="en"><text>foreign (from a different country)</text></gloss></sense><sense id="asing_1" guid="e3ccdb67-cad4-53e1-870b-ab411affe9dd"><grammatical-info value="Adjective"/><gloss lang="en"><text>foreign (belonging to a different culture)</text></gloss></sense><sense id="asing_2" guid="91f15af6-3808-5e2e-b033-952cdb075259"><grammatical-info value="Adjective"/><gloss lang="en"><text>foreign (in a place where it does not belong)</text></gloss></sense><sense id="asing_3" guid="86ec42dc-59c2-5a25-9792-28810e718aaf"><grammatical-info value="Adjective"/><gloss lang="en"><text>different</text></gloss></sense><sense id="asing_4" guid="8ce4fb2d-49db-5868-9f45-17eac4ae0898"><grammatical-info value="Adjective"/><gloss lang="en"><text>separated</text></gloss></sense><sense id="asing_5" guid="5c447b85-66c1-5b98-93c2-f745b97d186e"><grammatical-info value="Adjective"/><gloss lang="en"><text>weird</text></gloss></sense><sense id="asing_6" guid="d2b8e0b8-883e-5dc4-9cb3-e1ab6fe32a67"><grammatical-info value="Adjective"/><gloss lang="en"><text>awkward</text></gloss></sense></entry>
<entry id="asisten" guid="d15fb6d6-1d15-5de8-b118-79f47347d78f"><lexical-unit><form lang="id"><text>asisten</text></form></lexical-unit><trait name="morph-type" value="stem"/><sense id="asisten_0" guid="90f77ee1-6d72-59bc-ac3d-281cc66666df"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>assistant (someone who aids one another)</text></gloss></sense></entry>
<entry id="asli" guid="095ea094-7537-5710-8d56-06346d0db722"><lexical-unit><form lang="id"><text>asli</text></form></lexical-unit><trait name="morph-type" value="stem"/><sense id="asli_0" guid="57263dda-fbc5-5af2-9ee1-5e64bc506966"><grammatical-info value="Adjective"/><gloss lang="en"><text>original</text></gloss></sense><sense id="asli_1" guid="b5aa70aa-e239-54c7-8dfc-332820746023"><grammatical-info value="Adjective"/><gloss lang="en"><text>pure</text></gloss></sense><sense id="asli_2" guid="c117882e-dc5a-543a-a5b7-efd14368ac21"><grammatical-info value="Adjective"/><gloss lang="en"><text>native: Born or grown in the region in which it lives or is found; not foreign or imported</text></gloss></sense><sense id="asli_3" guid="353b1016-e747-522c-a3b2-f91329e8259c"><grammatical-info value="Adjective"/><gloss lang="en"><text>nature: The innate characteristics of a thing. What something will tend by its own constitution, to be or do. Distinct from what might be expected or intended</text></gloss></sense><sense id="asli_4" guid="a88e1122-86a5-57fb-b0cc-ea4d14a397f6"><grammatical-info value="Adjective"/><gloss lang="en"><text>origin</text></gloss></sense></entry>
