<entry id="bengkok" guid="b188718c-e787-51e9-99ac-1507b6f5cf10"><lexical-unit><form lang="id"><text>bengkok</text></form></lexical-unit><trait name="morph-type" value="stem"/><sense id="bengkok_0" guid="0afe1575-26af-5b79-9252-cdbb21b813ff"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>bent, dented</text></gloss></sense><sense id="bengkok_1" guid="55d32266-30f2-584a-8a4a-766e388a278c"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>bent, corrupt, dishonest</text></gloss></sense><sense id="bengkok_2" guid="1c1fdf48-2ec1-5152-aec8-23935748e87a"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>kidney dish, emesis basin: a shallow basin with a kidney-shaped base and sloping walls used in medical and surgical wards to receive soiled dressings and other medical waste, commonly known as Dutch nierbekken (“renal pelvis”, literally “kidney-shaped basin”)</text></gloss></sense><sense id="bengkok_3" guid="29bc076e-9c28-517e-ab74-448db434b00c"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>a village land, which is lent to the village head to be cultivated and harvested as a substitute for salary</text></gloss></sense></entry>
