<entry id="gali" guid="8c49ee35-8b32-55f8-a43f-01c29ff2d37b"><lexical-unit><form lang="id"><text>gali</text></form></lexical-unit><trait name="morph-type" value="stem"/><sense id="gali_0" guid="5ccf88ae-16f3-5e4c-97a5-7960869046b0"><grammatical-info value="Verb"/><gloss lang="en"><text>to dig (to move hard-packed earth out of the way)</text></gloss></sense><sense id="gali_1" guid="3e5dcf8b-fd58-5884-908b-a637208eab5e"><grammatical-info value="Verb"/><gloss lang="en"><text>galley: A long, slender ship propelled primarily by oars, whether having masts and sails or not; usually referring to rowed warships used in the Mediterranean from the 16th century until the modern era</text></gloss></sense><sense id="gali_2" guid="67b228e2-59fe-51d8-b3c4-15eaa54117fd"><grammatical-info value="Verb"/><gloss lang="en"><text>criminal</text></gloss></sense></entry>
