<entry id="hisop" guid="f933b0c2-cc06-55a4-b857-724a3193cd4b"><lexical-unit><form lang="id"><text>hisop</text></form></lexical-unit><trait name="morph-type" value="stem"/><sense id="hisop_0" guid="5459b4b6-f92a-5b5c-995d-7a780a9701db"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>hyssop:</text></gloss></sense><sense id="hisop_1" guid="f2ef4b8c-7b07-5fd4-b723-7ec1e01593ae"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>any of several aromatic bushy herbs, of the genus Hyssopus, native to Southern Europe and once used medicinally</text></gloss></sense><sense id="hisop_2" guid="ce2e8842-1173-541e-ab3f-49a32fbaf3ff"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>specifically, Hyssopus officinalis</text></gloss></sense><sense id="hisop_3" guid="349bc377-b29a-5e88-9538-5608ba4bb64b"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>any of several similar plants:</text></gloss></sense><sense id="hisop_4" guid="bb138ad3-c3c9-536c-8bd1-8f884028a448"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>blue giant hyssop (Agastache foeniculum)</text></gloss></sense><sense id="hisop_5" guid="d9b3bceb-2dca-5933-80d4-374cced04187"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>sagebrush (Artemisia spp.)</text></gloss></sense><sense id="hisop_6" guid="3be29618-6373-519d-b12c-b5c67ad41d86"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>a plant used used for sprinkling of blood or water in purification rituals and at Passover (Origanum syriacum)</text></gloss></sense><sense id="hisop_7" guid="d012dc61-2170-5bd2-bec1-35843d9dd4d8"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>aspergillum, the holy-water sprinkle: an implement, in the form of a brush or of a rod with a perforated container, for sprinkling holy water</text></gloss></sense></entry>
