<entry id="ku" guid="d697a812-6d1d-520c-949d-4051fbbcd4ac"><lexical-unit><form lang="id"><text>ku</text></form></lexical-unit><trait name="morph-type" value="stem"/><sense id="ku_0" guid="cc3a4689-b69f-58da-902b-426febc11ac4"><grammatical-info value="Pronoun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>apheretic form of aku</text></gloss></sense><sense id="ku_1" guid="0a5517cf-904e-50fe-96c3-7d00b4bf1f98"><grammatical-info value="Pronoun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>Ang ku kueh: a small round or oval-shaped Chinese sweet dumpling with soft, sticky glutinous rice flour skin wrapped around a sweet central filling</text></gloss></sense><sense id="ku_2" guid="824051f9-7c6e-5568-b880-432fa50fb1bc"><grammatical-info value="Pronoun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>synonym of desa (“village”)</text></gloss></sense><sense id="ku_3" guid="0119f6f4-ab65-52d1-8687-798ab07c5c31"><grammatical-info value="Pronoun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>alternative spelling of -ku</text></gloss></sense><sense id="ku_4" guid="8e9f062d-8719-5666-8d3c-9ee757f2754f"><grammatical-info value="Pronoun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>a surname from Hakka</text></gloss></sense><sense id="ku_5" guid="f2e73d04-9da3-5153-9d4b-e7958ca3de38"><grammatical-info value="Pronoun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>initialism of keadaan umum (“general appearance”)</text></gloss></sense><sense id="ku_6" guid="fbd3adf0-c111-515e-9fce-2d396b258b94"><grammatical-info value="Pronoun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>initialism of kondisi umum (“general appearance”)</text></gloss></sense></entry>
