<entry id="kuil" guid="63b5d7a6-8690-5418-87dc-0f3758063ffa"><lexical-unit><form lang="id"><text>kuil</text></form></lexical-unit><trait name="morph-type" value="stem"/><sense id="kuil_0" guid="bd8dcbc7-4c8f-51a8-b2fc-761352de2612"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>temple, a house of worship of religions, except for Balinese Hinduism (pura)</text></gloss></sense><sense id="kuil_1" guid="eb862206-58b8-5cf2-8c28-d879c638dda3"><grammatical-info value="Noun"/><gloss lang="en"><text>shrine, a holy or sacred place dedicated to a specific deity, ancestor, hero, martyr, saint, or similar figure of awe and respect, at which said figure is venerated or worshipped</text></gloss></sense></entry>
